## 🛠️ Setup & Installation

### 1️⃣ Clone Repo
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/network-compliance-automation.git
cd network-compliance-automation
2️⃣ Install Dependencies
bash
Copy code
pip install -r requirements.txt
Dependencies include:

netmiko → connect to devices

pymongo → interact with MongoDB

pyyaml → load YAML compliance rules

django → web interface

3️⃣ Setup MongoDB
Start MongoDB locally or use MongoDB Atlas.

Create collections:

devices → stores inventory

configs → stores running configs

4️⃣ Add Devices
Example devices.json entry:

json
Copy code
{
  "hostname": "csr1000v-1",
  "ip": "10.10.20.48",
  "vendor": "cisco",
  "username": "developer",
  "password": "C1sco12345"
}
5️⃣ Define Rules
Example rules.yaml:

yaml
Copy code
ntp:
  description: "NTP server configured"
  must_have:
    - "ntp server"
  must_not_have: []

snmp:
  description: "SNMP must not use default public strings"
  must_have: []
  must_not_have:
    - "snmp-server community public"
    - "snmp-server community private"

banner:
  description: "MOTD banner present"
  must_have:
    - "banner motd"
  must_not_have: []
6️⃣ Run Scripts
Fetch config:

bash
Copy code
python scripts/fetch_config.py
Save to MongoDB:

bash
Copy code
python scripts/config_find.py
Check compliance:

bash
Copy code
python scripts/compliance_check.py
7️⃣ Django Web UI
Run server:

bash
Copy code
cd django_app
python manage.py runserver
Visit: http://127.0.0.1:8000/

📊 Flow Diagram
mermaid
Copy code
flowchart TD
    A[Devices Inventory in MongoDB] -->|Fetch Configs| B[Fetch Config Script]
    B -->|Store Running Configs| C[Configs Collection in MongoDB]
    C -->|Apply Rules| D[Compliance Check Script]
    D -->|Results| E[Django Web UI]
    E -->|Reports| F[User/Engineer]
